nce >= 0.8\n\nOutput your evaluation as JSON matching the NetworkEvaluation schema.\n", "user_message": "Evaluate this synthesis network:\n\nTARGET MOLECULE: Serine\nOVERALL STRATEGY: This network targets serine as a prebiotic product formed predominantly through glycolaldehyde-centered Strecker chemistry, while embedding that route within a broader interconnected prebiotic network supported by the literature. Hydrothermal chemistry supplies reduced C1-C3 feedstocks such as formate, formaldehyde, glycolaldehyde, pyruvate, HCN, and NH3 on iron-sulfur and oxide minerals. Surface environments then concentrate and transform these molecules through formose, cyanosulfidic photochemistry, HCN oligomerization, Strecker aminonitrile formation, and hydrolysis under mineral-assisted wet-dry and UV-driven conditions. Biochemical/prebiotic stages convert serine and serinonitrile into downstream products including phosphoserine, peptides, and cysteine precursors, while also allowing reverse decomposition links back to pyruvate, glycine, and formaldehyde consistent with serine fragility. The result is a bipartite network with multiple convergent routes to the key hubs HCN, formaldehyde, glycolaldehyde, serinonitrile, and pyruvate, and 10 distinct valid pathways to serine spanning hydrothermal, surface, impact/spark analog, and cyanosulfidic contexts.\n\nMOLECULES (20 nodes):\n  - mol_001: CO2 (carbon dioxide) [starting]\n  - mol_002: H2 (hydrogen) [starting]\n  - mol_003: NH3 (ammonia) [starting]\n  - mol_004: HCN (hydrogen cyanide) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_005: CH2O2 (formic acid) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_006: CH2O (formaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_007: C2H4O2 (glycolaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_008: C3H6O3 (glyceraldehyde) [intermediate]\n  - mol_009: C3H4O3 (pyruvic acid) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_010: C2H5NO (formaldimine) [intermediate]\n  - mol_011: C3H4N2O (serinonitrile) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_012: C3H8N2O2 (serinamide) [intermediate]\n  - mol_013: C3H7NO3 (serine) [target]\n  - mol_014: C3H4N2 (dehydroalanine nitrile) [intermediate]\n  - mol_015: C2H5NO2 (glycine) [intermediate]\n  - mol_016: C3H7NO5P (phosphoserine) [intermediate]\n  - mol_017: C3H5NO4 (serylserine) [intermediate]\n  - mol_018: CH3NO (formamide) [intermediate]\n  - mol_019: C4H5N2O2 (N-formylserinonitrile) [intermediate]\n  - mol_020: H2S (hydrogen sulfide) [starting]\n\nREACTIONS (20 nodes):\n  - rxn_001: mol_001, mol_002 -> mol_005 (Hydrothermal CO2 reduction to formate on greigite) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_002: mol_001, mol_002 -> mol_006 (Hydrothermal Fischer-Tropsch-type generation of formaldehyde) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_003: mol_001, mol_003, mol_020 -> mol_004 (Hydrothermal HCN generation/release from iron-sulfide mediated nitrogen-carbon reduction) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_004: mol_001, mol_002 -> mol_009 (Hydrothermal pyruvate synthesis from reduced carbon on iron minerals) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_005: mol_006 -> mol_007 (Surface formose formation of glycolaldehyde from formaldehyde) [Surface]\n  - rxn_006: mol_004, mol_020 -> mol_007, mol_008 (Surface cyanosulfidic photoreductive homologation to glycolaldehyde and glyceraldehyde) [Surface]\n  - rxn_007: mol_004 -> mol_018 (Surface photochemical hydration of HCN to formamide) [Surface]\n  - rxn_008: mol_007, mol_003 -> mol_010 (Surface glycolaldehyde imination to formaldimine-type precursor pool) [Surface]\n  - rxn_009: mol_007, mol_003, mol_004 -> mol_011 (Surface Strecker synthesis of serinonitrile from glycolaldehyde) [Surface]\n  - rxn_010: mol_007, mol_004, mol_018 -> mol_019 (Surface formamide-protected cyanide addition to N-formylserinonitrile) [Surface]\n  - rxn_011: mol_011 -> mol_012 (Hydrolysis of serinonitrile to serinamide) [Surface]\n  - rxn_012: mol_012 -> mol_013 (Hydrolysis of serinamide to serine) [Surface]\n  - rxn_013: mol_019 -> mol_013 (Deformylation and hydrolysis of N-formylserinonitrile to serine) [Surface]\n  - rxn_014: mol_011 -> mol_014 (Biochemical